quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  49,1,"O believers! Do not proceed ňĻin any matterňļ before ňĻa decree fromňļ Allah and His Messenger. And fear Allah. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  49,2,"O believers! Do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet, nor speak loudly to him as you do to one another,¬†or your deeds will become void while you are unaware"
  49,3,"Indeed, those who lower their voices in the presence of Allah‚Äôs Messenger are the ones whose hearts Allah has refined for righteousness. They will have forgiveness and a great reward"
  49,4,"Indeed, most of those who call out to you ňĻO Prophetňļ from outside ňĻyourňļ private quarters have no understanding ňĻof mannersňļ"
  49,5,"Had they been patient until you could come out to them, it would have certainly been better for them. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  49,6,"O believers, if an evildoer brings you any news, verify ňĻitňļ so you do not harm people unknowingly, becoming regretful for what you have done"
  49,7,"And keep in mind that Allah‚Äôs Messenger is ňĻstillňļ in your midst. If he were to yield to you in many matters, you would surely suffer ňĻthe consequencesňļ.¬†But Allah has endeared faith to you, making it appealing in your hearts. And He has made disbelief, rebelliousness, and disobedience detestable to you. Those are the ones rightly guided"
  49,8,"ňĻThis isňļ a bounty and a blessing from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  49,9,"And if two groups of believers fight each other, then make peace between them. But if one of them transgresses against the other, then fight against the transgressing group until they ňĻare willing toňļ submit to the rule of Allah. If they do so, then make peace between both ňĻgroupsňļ in all fairness and act justly. Surely Allah loves those who uphold justice"
  49,10,"The believers are but one brotherhood, so make peace between your brothers. And be mindful of Allah so you may be shown mercy"